reviews.text: Very good store, clean very clean, the service  is quick and the preparation  is done to whatever  you want. They say burger king you can have it your way(I don't  know about that). Subway you really get it your way they don't hide behind a wall everything  is right there for you to see

I usually come in after or before a workout sesh. I get the same sandwich every time. This time they had flies around the food and it stood on my sandwich, meanwhile they did nothing to get the flies off my sandwich. They also get upset when they don’t receive tips. I also get different prices for the same exact sandwich I get which is fishy to me. They always seem to increase the price on me when I always get the same thing.

Never ordering food from here again .! I had to keep calling and calling the store just to tell them that the app keeps saying my food has been delivered but nothing was outside . The lady was very disrespectful hung up in my face then when I called again she said she can cancel my order because no one wanted to deliver it . There was also a man in the background telling her that if my number didn’t match what’s on the app then they can’t give me my food .! If I could give them 0 stars I would ! Very unprofessional
I love the footlong meatball sub with pepper jack cheese with oregano and parmesan cheese and chipotle southwest sauce! I sometimes add more but imo subway always hits home!

Was on my lunch break on Easter Sunday. When I walked in the guy was sitting in the back. I said hello .. he just looked a me while he was eating, said something then continued to watch videos on his phone. I then said can i have a sandwich? He said rudely “I’m eating and continued to watch his videos on his phone”. What’s the point of being open then getting rude with your customers? I WILL be contacting corporate!

name: America's Best Wings
vicinity: Addison Plaza, 6264 Central Avenue, Seat Pleasant

reviews.text: Loved the food . ordered steak & cheese and fries. will come again to fresh wings

This location to me is not up to par of the franchise Americas best has become.  I went here today and ordered the grilled catfish and shrimp meal. Both items reached live they had been cooked this morning and just warmed up when i ordered.  The catfish  was a little hard and burned, the shrimp was burned hard and tasted old. I love americas best but this location i will definitely never visit again

Steak and cheese was good, but would like to have had more steak. My son brung this home for me to try. My expectations are from a 90s carryout steak and cheese were they packed it on. Would still go there though.
Food tasted weird, and they didnt really care. Had to ask for a different flavor. Wouldnt recommend
They are really good , I am impressed about their service . Food was awesome. Thanks

Probably one of the worst Dunkin’ Donuts I visited. Paid almost $6 for a sandwich to not have any bacon on it after waiting in the drive thru for almost 30 mins. Recieved my coffee cold and only halfway filled. All in all a horrible location and I will not be returning.

Ordered ahead using the app. Visited location and order could not be found and the manager walked away. They did not know how to give support on the app to see previous orders (that should be part of training). They simply dismissed me. Then, I notice an order sitting on the counter and that was it. Asked why the drink was half full and was informed, bc it took so long to pick up the order.  Not everyone was rude, but I had to get loud to get assistance. This is not how you want to start the morning. I was not going to leave this review but when I got to my destination, the order was not made correctly although the recipient was correct. What a shame this is the service they give in our community. We deserved better.

Worse Dunkin’ Donuts I have ever been too. Went through drive through but no one spoke over loud speaker to ever take my order. Drove around and no one was at window. Had to call phone for guy to come to window and then for him to tell me that I had to drive back around to be helped. He was very rude and extremely disrespectful. I left without being helped.

Terrible customer service. Served us old spoiled, watered down tea. When I told the cashier, it literally did not care to replace our drinks. He said he only had coffee drinks. I just drove off because he didn’t care to accommodate us even we frequent that spot.

This location sucks!!! Save your time, Save your energy, Save your money! It needs to be shutdown to be honest. The workers are usually chilling not paying any attention to customers and just overall extremely slow service.

name: China Chef Enterprises
vicinity: 5925 Martin Luther King Junior Highway, Seat Pleasant

reviews.text: average Chinese Carryout prices are not what they use to be and the quality of the food is mediocre. Chicken wings prepared well done and crispy with hot sauce was tasty I must say.
Went in for one of my friends to get her food me personally I don't like their food I like Far East

I found i could give -5 stars i would. Terrible everything. Terrible attidude when i was trynna order. She was unnecessarily rude. The food was just bad, everything it was just bad. I was very disappointed when i got it what else can i say.
I ordered hot and sour soup, it was horrible. I asked for spicy singapore noodles, but they were bland. Hospital food! I won't be back.

Always open too the Striving Soul's of our community especially late night when mostly everyone else is shut down too us there food is always on point I feed my family, Friends and strangers with there menu 😋 😊 plus they give free Big Liter Soda with $30 purchases. Check em out you won't be disappointed.

This is the very last time I order from this location. Corporate need to come in and find out what they are doing to provide such poor service. For a location only minutes away I should not be waiting 3 hours for a pizza. I know on Fridays it can be a little busy, hence the reason I ordered early. But here it is almost 9pm. The tracker obviously doesn’t work as “Terry” have been quality checking my pizza since 6:16pm. I would rather just boil some hot dogs than to order from this store again!

Believe the reviews! Delivery is not the best option for this location. Food took two hours to arrive and it was cold. Tracker said it was quality checked a hour and a half before it arrived. Food arrived and pizza was wrong. The pizza insurance on the app doesn’t do anything if you make a note about the issue. If you decide to order from here pick up might be your best option over delivery.

I don't normally rate places but this one needed this rating. Not only did we not get our food for over an hour, the food we got was nothing like we had ordered. We had two medium pizzas, hand tossed with chicken, bacon, and one had mushrooms, with some cheese bread. What we got was one thin crust pepperoni and sausage pizza and one plain cheese hand tossed. We also had sauces in our order and those didn't even come with them!

I wish I could give it a zero. It’s was utterly disgusting looking and tasting. I literally had an inch of cheese on my pizza it wasn’t even fully cut , the wings weren’t done. I told them to Re cook them. 15 minutes later they’re just as soggy and not done. Honestly I wouldn’t even give that food to a homeless person let alone my children. I would never visit or order from this location again. I will never order from any dominoes. I’m completely disgusted by the poor service and disgusting looking and nasty tasting food. I’ll just stick with ledos or papa johns. I wish I could save everyone from ever visiting this location. Two thumbs down. Don’t waste your time or money

This is a horrible experience.  My order was placed at 2:58pm EST.  The current time is 3:59pm EST.  The estimator is estimating my food order to come at 4:43pm EST.

More than likely, I will be receiving a COLD after paying alot of money for food.  This is ridiculous and unacceptable.

I will be writing the corporater office as well as post my reviews on several blogs.  I am entirely dissapointed with Dominos and you have just lost a customer.

Sincerely,

A very dissappointed and former customer!
Good food
My meal was fresh hot and tasty. The staff was friendly and the drive- thru was pretty quick with my order.

This is the worst Taco Bell ever.  The customer service is very unprofessional and your orders are always wrong.  The mentality of the staff and manager, Andre Milton is a disgrace.  The manager argued with me calling me confused, and out of professional name after I try to explain to him charging me $39 for 12 Supreme Nachos was incorrect. After me waiting patiently for over 25min trying to place a order He asked me to get out of his line because I wasn't getting service and called security on me.  The security apologized to me for the harsh unprofessional treatment my family and I received and mention the store has been getting complaints from the so call manager all day, which he shouts all my manager is never here so complain all you want. Unfortunately, customer service is hard to come by in a black community. I will never spend another dime at this unprofessional ghetto Taco Bell. If no stars was a option I would have chose that.

The cashiers tell everyone to order from the kiosks.  I suppose the kiosks can be convenient; however, it is generally much quicker to order through a cashier because they are familiar & experienced with the system.
There are also various modifications, substitutions & requests which the kiosks do not accommodate, and when there aren't any employees taking orders it is often difficult too get someone to come to front to tell them.

I'm very happy that the Mexican pizza is back!  However, the one I got today was rather pathetic looking and the ingredients were not portioned correctly.  They also neglected to provide me a utensil to eat it with and there were none at the condiment station.

I would give this place a zero. Reason one is they are not open on time for breakfast. Reason two is that their food tast old not brand new or fresh. Reason three is their customer is horrible on the weekends it be youngster in their playing around like it a dam children playground while people be patiently waiting for their order to be taken. Last reason their food is to expensive for dam food that not enough for one person . Go somewhere for better food.That it Thank you please give this place a 1out of 5 stars

Drive through, was asked to move back from the window after paying, then to drive back up for my meal. My drink was incorrect, she fixed that, but I should have cheacked my food, it was all wrong. Meat when I ordered vegetarian. Too late by the time I was home to drive back and fix. Short staffed and distracted employees.

name: Far East Restaurant
vicinity: 5920 Martin Luther King Junior Highway, Seat Pleasant

reviews.text: No complaints. Good food. Will go again.

Please don't buy there.
I ordered a roasted pork and when I got home this is what I get a bunch of unions and peppers and about 10 pieces of us quarter size looking pork and it tasted terrible

If I could give no stars I would , I ordered off Uber eats I got 3 wings and fried rice , when I opened the food it smelled spoiled but I’m hungry I went ahead and ate my chicken when I bit into it , it’s tasted like it was fried in old grease , the rice tasted old it was hard as hell . Would never eat from here again , thanks to Uber for giving me my money back they only thing good was the mix tea

I landed on this restaurant after a long search on Grubhub. Because it was a rainy day and I was tired of looking I thought I’d just settle for carry out but the spot I usually order from was closed. So I thought let’s try something new. I ordered Sesame chicken and Singapore Noodles, 2 of their “signature dishes” that i didn’t think it was possible for them to mess up, but honey they did just that. The Noodle dish was made up of the slimiest meat they could find, it was under seasoned and they didn’t even bother to cut up the chicken it was one long piece. The sesame chicken was dark inside and tasted gamy, it tasted like old meat they fried it up and tossed it in a pineapple sesame sauce. I was beyond dissatisfied. It was after my experience that I actually read the reviews and judging from what I’m seeing, no one should order from here.

Had to order online. I should have taken the hint
The food you get is not at all like it is pictured. Bland and doughy. I ordered general tso's shrimp. When it was delivered the sauce which was supposed to have been cooked with the shrimp was spilled all over my other food in the bag. When I opened the shrimp it was wrapped in a lot of batter. I had trouble finding any shrimp. I had to drive back to get this watery syrup they gave me for sauce. They would not deliver my messed up order. Told me that any complaints had to be made to the company.
I will never ever spend any money at this establishment. They don't deserve my business
We live in a food dessert. These other business owners take advantage of that and contribute nothing to our neighborhood. Think my neighbors! Make other choices.

This restaurant is extremely dirty. I should have known not to eat here when I saw the floors were dirty and the counter top had stains. The walls even have stains. I ordered a general tos chicken lunch special. When I bit into a chicken chunk, a bug was discovered. Cooked into the chicken. I will be reporting this restaurant. When I went to go get my money back, they complained I ate out of it already.

Called in order for pickup.Food was ready quickly and was available for pick up when I arrived.We got Barbecue chicken with white rice,shrimp basket with shrimp fired rice and wings with fried rice.As always meals were excellent.
My family and I love China Sky's dishes. The food is good and the price is reasonable.Chicken wings, shrimp basket and Crab sticks are recommended.

Good for what I like. For this restaurant, they don’t do everything great, but what they do well, they do really well. The fried rice is great. Pork fried rice and chicken wings is what I get at least once or twice per week for. I never have any complaints. What I can say is that the people who run this restaurant and understand they are in a competitive business. So they bring their A game, which keeps me from not going to the other Chinese food store right down the street.

Food delivered improperly packaged, items spilling all over bag. No utensils. No dumpling sauce (included with dumplings).  No egg rolls (included with combo).  No duck sauce included, no mustard included.

Food quality subpar, tastes like you already let it sit for a day and reheated it.

Do not recommend. Avoid. Waste of money.   Take the time to make the food, and package the food properly.

My boyfriend and I wanted something different for dinner and neither one of us were in the mood to cook. My boyfriend pulled up some black-owned business in the area and decided to give Rosebuds a try. I am not a big rib person but overall, the food was good. I elected for the pork platter with greens and mac-n-cheese and my boyfriend chose the beef platter with hamburger beans and potato salad. They mixed cabbage with their greens which was the first time ever having that combination it was good. The hamburger beans are pork and beans with hamburger meat… it was just that nothing spectacular. The mac and cheese is mediocre, personally I like mine extra cheeeeesy, ribs were slightly tough but still edible. If you have a large vehicle like ours, parking will be difficult considering the limited parking available. 3 out of 5 stars.

I googled ribs near me and chose this place from the listing due to it being black owned and the reviews.  I got the smoked chicken / rib combo with collard greens. The ribs were so tender and just overall good! I would go back for ribs. The chicken, however, was not seasoned but was very tender. The service was dope.

I popped by this spot because it's suppose to be somewhat local. It's also a B.O.B. (Black-owned business) so I decided to patronize it and support. There are few positives because unfortunately this place needs work...

1) Location, location, location, is everything and this place would probably operate WAY better if it a) had accessible free parking, b) wasn't next to a sketchy/dangerous liquor store w/police onsite 🚓, c) in the hood, d) wasn't rocking the bulletproof plastic front, 2) The food 🤔, I bought the burger w/cheese added, fries, and ribs sandwich (1 pound.) Why couldn't the burger be fresh and grilled?! You literally couldn't take the time to do that, and then had the nerve to glance up to SEE if I saw you microwave the burger/ribs?! The gall 🙄...,
3) the staff in the back WTH aren't they working? If they wanna gossip and keke, they need to act like they're busy!; 4) the poor family of 3 in back of me were waiting for like 10 minutes (no staff members tended to them until you finished processing my payment), 5) the place could use a wipe down and actual Coronavirus precautions in place (pandemic active still in May 2022), and lastly 6) instead of pandemic vacations in 2022 to the Caribbean 🏝️,  put that effort in your restaurant and then it could truly be a household name - instead of having food I won't let near my household again...

Overall, have pride where you have your business and stop cutting corners. This was such a bad first impression, not just as a business - but as a Black-owned business. Cut down the plastic please and use paper or compostable packaging and no plastic bags! Mother Earth deserves the best! The positives are few and far between: such as the wings being huge (didn't buy, just saw) and the prices are cool.

Bonus: 🍅Why does the ketchup have an apple scent 🍎?
The best rib’s I’ve ever had the sauce was amazing 🤩 and the service was wonderful I felt very welcome 🤗 definitely going back and telling all my friends 🤣🥰

Ordered 2 pans of Macaroni and Cheese for my daughters birthday celebration and it was a Huge hit with all guests in attendance.

The staff was friendly and courteous  as well as the price is very affordable.  I will definitely be ordering again for other upcoming events.

name: Jerry's Carryout
vicinity: 5702 Martin Luther King Junior Highway, Capitol Heights

reviews.text: Cheap eats, quick turnaround time on food. Accurate and efficient, and they take cash app. Could ask for more, but then would it be worth it 🤷🏾‍♂️
The are slow in giving your then when you get the food sometime it's not right they give you chicken that been sitting to long it's not all of that.

This establishment is terrible. The young lady that assisted us with our order was very rude. We paid for our order and when we came back to check the status of our food she implied that we did not pay for our meal. The communication was not there and we tried to get clarity but the young lady was very upset and would not listen. Thankfully there was another employee that was able to explain in detail about the bill that is was partially paid and the add on was not included. It was very frustrating that the customer service was not there and I will never eat at this establishment again.
Good location good food and good people right down the street.

If i could give this place a 0 i would!

THEY LITERALLY ALWAYS HAVE HAIR IN THEIR FOOD!
So disgusting!

Food was hot and fresh as it should have been after an extensive wait inside the store trying to avoid the usual long wait in the drive through.  Management is to blame they definitely don't posses a sense of urgency in taking care of the customers.  So prepare to wait and pray your food turns out to be worth it.

We downloaded the app to place our order for pickup and when we arrived at Popeyes, we found out that the app didn’t process our order completely... Thanks to the manager for understanding our technical experience with the app and she completed our order in a timely manner..! It will be appreciated if Popeyes can fix any Bug issues and updates with the app.
This Popeyes is always on point. I never have a problem with my food. I wait a little bit but it's Popeyes and my food is always hot and fresh. The staff is cool, Hood but cool.

Go somewhere else believe me, I've been going to this popeyes for years and tonight I went in to pickup an online order after waiting for 15 minutes for the employees to fill up the boxes of chicken, I picked my order up and it was just sad food was missing wrong items were in the bag, the worker said she wasn't worried about my food ahe was worried about the food she was making and clearly we then got into an verbal altercation I have great experience with the day ctee and that manager is great but after 4 pm quality of food and customer service is gone

This is the worse pope's in the DMV I usually don't leave reviews but today was a must this popeys always has a line wrapped around the corner not because people love the food but because the service is horrible, I go on the inside tonight and they have no chicken ready I mean none..this is unacceptable never have I seen the chicken racks empty at any other peopeys when the chicken get low the cooks prepare for more chicken and keep things in rotation people came in with mobile orders and was told 15 minutes and end up waiting 45 minutes and the workers had the nerve to get smart and disrespectful to customers complaining about food that they paid for so I left I don't wanna spend my money with popeys  changes need to be made ASAP.

name: Keith & Sons Soul Food
vicinity: 5948 Martin Luther King Junior Highway, Seat Pleasant

reviews.text: What happened to this place? The food is definitely not the same. It was a true waste of money. Their food used to taste like it was cooked with soulful love and it used to be packed. Went in yesterday and there was only three of us. The fish was over cooked and salty, the string beans were straight from the can with no flavor and the potato salad was warm even though it came from the fridge. Never again.

So glad I finally stopped in to check this place out. The dishes below included the Whiting dinner with corn and Mac & cheese. Chicken wing dinner with Mac & Cheese and mashed potatoes with gravy. The third dinner was pork chops mashed potatoes and yams. It was all delicious and the portions are huge. You certainly can't go away hungry. Looking forward to visiting soon again.

Four of us stopped in for lunch on a whim.
Turns out this place serves up some pretty amazing food.

My partner got the breaded pork chops, I got the half chicken. The sides are also super delicious as well (pictured is the mac & cheese and corn).

The prices are on point as well. We got a ton of food for the price. (For reference: the McDonald's across the street charges almost the same price for far less food.)

We will definitely be back soon to try out the breakfast options!

We got candied yams and they gave us whole sweet potatoes in sauce. They were also really stringy. The fried chicken was unseasoned. The macaroni and cheese was watery. Overpriced and disappointing. Cutting corners and it shows.

Its packed everyday for breakfast. The food is good and they give you plenty. The service is good too. I recommend the BLT , waffles,  the big breakfast and the hash. I haven't had lunch or dinner here but I hear its pretty good. 4 stars for no AC. There are 2 big fans but in the summer its still hot. But other than that its a good place to get take out.

I love the woman and her husband really sweet people i come here often and she always takes cares of me really a community Carry out never had problems with the food always hot, never had hair or bugs etc i do wish their half and half was not from bottles but ill let that slide lol 🤣
the food here is delicious. The large potions are huge, and enough for two people. Small place, not fancy but they make excellent take out.
LOVE THE FOOD! THE PRICES ARE AMAZING!!! THE young lady that takes the orders is always so nice and remembers my and my son's orders. Very professional.
Horrible service. Cross contamination. Rude. Just nasty. Do not go here. The will cook everything on the same grill using the same utensils. Then get mad when you call them on it.
They work extremely fast especially with how many orders they have and little amounts of workers

I won’t go here again. I bought snacks and you can tell by the taste that it was old! The soda became flat within minutes and tasted funny. The M&M’s tasted old like they had them for months. Only thing fresh was the chips of course.
People are very nice and kind it's a neighborly store just like the stores in the past what was lost long time ago
Ok place

I got a bunch of food for my family and it was amazing. The customer service was great, the food was fast and fresh. There is a variety of food and it’s all amazing!! Everything I had was so good! I highly recommend.

Y’all get the chicken biriyani or the lamb or is soooo freaking good. I didn’t know what to get and I was super sketched out bc of the area BUT the food is phenomenal, they’re amazing, tell them Sheila Sent you.

I found the “restaurant near me” online for our last evening in town, they definitely did not disappoint. Our group ordered a few different meals, all were on point. We were trying to find something everyone would like and ABCAW fit the bill. We checked the reviews. We saw the variety of dishes and their eyes got big! Everything was tasty, the; chicken curry, salmon curry, cake desserts, vegetable spring rolls, vegetable fried rice, mango lassi and drinks. Yes Yes they thanked me! ABCAW, kudos!! (We’re gonna get breakfast there on our way out)

This carryout is a gem hidden in the cut. I don't know what they put in the food but you will be ADDICTED after ordering, here. Instead of chicken, do something different and try the fried fish and waffles. Trust me, it will be the best decision you ever made! You can't go wrong with the salmon fried rice, which is always on point and, unlike, another reviewer, I don't mind finding a clove or cardamom in my food. That just let's me know I'm dealing with authentic food. I don't eat chicken or beef so can't comment on that but according to other reviews on here, you won't be disappointed. Great service whether ordering over the phone or picking up an online order. 10 out of 10, all day

IT WAS A HORRIBLE EXPERIENCE. I ordered 5 pc. chicken and fries. The chicken meat was dried out and the fries was hard af. Asked for mambo sauce on the side and only received one for 5 wings but gave me unlimited supply of ketchup. And told me to come back back if I needed more like this was gon be A1. Smh. I ate most of it cause I’m hi but it was nasty

Ordered the honey lemon old bay wings + Mac and cheese &  yams. Staff and storefront clean and friendly. Def a neighborhood spot. Food was made to order so took bout 20min, I’d recommend calling it in if time is an issue. Food was hot and seasoned well. Def gonna check out some other dishes . Cop’d the peach cobbler too . Yum

I didn't know what to expect.  But, oh boy; it met my expectations of good food. It was delicious!  I will definitely go back. I ordered the salmon, cabbage and kale greens. Family, please keep up the good work! This was my fist visit and not my last. I will tell everybody I know about your business.  Please don't stop doing what you're doing and pass your knowledge, wisdom and skills down.

I had my food delivered.  Once I received my order, I notice I didn’t have any condiments ( tarter sauce, ketchup, etc) or utensils.  My dessert was also missing from my order.  Addie was able to make the price adjustment for the missing item.  Nonetheless, the food tasted good.  It’s best when you go and pick up your food yourself because you get the chance see and make sure you get everything that you want.

It was our 1st visit on 11/21/22...we had a salmon dinner with cabbage and Mac n cheese....wingette dinner with double greens.😋The food was so good better than we expected. We was looking for a soulful food place and we arent looking anymore. We tried the pink lemonade half and half...so good ....the cornbread and customer service also on point. Looking forward to eating here again

Love this hidden gem. Food is cooked to order, comes out hot and bursting with taste.

A lot of family love in the air and the customer service has been above and beyond every visit.

Homeade desserts and reasonable prices.

In no way does this orange chicken resemble the one on the websites page. There was almost no sauce making it dry and disgusting to eat as it just tasted like chicken with an orange after taste due to the orange slices as well as the chicken being very thin and having little to no meat. I am heavily dissatisfied with what I received and would not recommend eating here.

General Moe’s Chicken was good, had a great spice to it. However the wait for the food took entirely too long. I ordered at 12:08pm and did not get my food until 1:40pm, despite them telling me that it would be ready at 12:40pm. On top of that the chicken and broccoli was poorly packed in the wrong container and leaked garlic sauce through the carryout bag on to my car seat. Blaq Dragon needs to get some things figured out logistically before it can be a viable take-out option.
Absolutely delicious. They do it just right here the food is FRESH the portions are perfect and its not too salty like most places. Excellent customer service and a great friendly environment.
Havent eaten here yet. I heard about this place on YouTube and plan to go when I'm in Maryland but I support black owned business. Here to show my support✊🏾
The food is everything. I will be ordering again. It is worth it. Just wish you were open more often.
